        <section>
          <h2>Our Students Are Motivated To:</h2>
          <ul class="rewards-list">
            <li>improve/maintain academic performance</li>
            <li>attend school regularly</li>
            <li>participate in after-school tutoring</li>

            <li>
              avoid behaviors that lead to negative <br /> referrals and suspensions
            </li>
            <li>contemplate a more positive future</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div> -->
      <div class="photo-card-container">
        <img
          class="photo-card-img"
          src={paddleBoarding}
          alt="students paddle boarding on a lake as the sun sets"
        />
        <!-- <div class="photo-card"></div> -->
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="rewards-container">
      <div class="rewards-card">
        <!-- <div class="rewards-curtain">
          <img class="rewards-icon" src={medals} alt="a stack of medals" />
        </div> -->
        <p>
          Students experience their power through the successful completion of
          challenges that generate rewards and incentives.
        </p>
        <img class="rewards-icon" src={medals} alt="a stack of medals" />
      </div>
      <div class="rewards-card">
        <p>
          Community service challenges are converted into employment
          opportunities when organizations like <br /><a
            href="https://ohiomeansjobs.ohio.gov/home/">Ohio Means Jobs</a
          > interview students in May.
        </p>
        <img class="rewards-icon" src={suitcase} alt="a stack of medals" />
      </div>
      <div class="rewards-card">
        <p>
          Students form new relationships with Lorain County businesses and grow
          their entrepreneurship skills through positive reinforcement.
        </p>
        <img class="rewards-icon" src={partners} alt="a stack of medals" />
      </div>
      <div class="rewards-card">
        <p>
          Students will realize that personal progress can be acquired through
          leadership training, proper mindset, college prep and community
          service.
        </p>
        <img
          class="rewards-icon"
          src={head}
          alt="a stack of medals"
          style="color: green;"
        />
      </div>
      <!-- <p>
        Our goal is to motivate Students to want to meet outside of school for
        two or more days per week to include fieldtrips for a total of 10 hours
        each week, rides to/from included (this would be in addition to any in
        school hours of training requested by the LCSD – currently 5-25 per
        week). Meeting hours will be after school on Thursdays (2:30pm-5:30pm)
        at Lorain High School and 11am-4pm on Saturdays which will include
